==English==
===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /藞da蕣n藢ra瑟t/

===Adverb===
'''downright'''
#{{colloquial}} [[really]], [[actually]], [[quite]]
#:*He wasn't just cool to me -- he was '''downright''' rude.

====Usage notes====
'''Downright''' is used to [[emphasize]] the following [[adjective]], which is usually about some [[negative]] quality.